    <h2>Chat</h2>
    <textarea rows="4" cols="50">
        > Jon: Anyone wanna pair?
        > anyone: sure
        > ...
    </textarea>
    <br>
    When a user adds himself to the queue, then a new row is added to the table, 
    and the fields for project description and Available Until will be clearly waiting for data. 
    So the user can set the project description and Available Until fields, similar to adding a new comment into slack or Disqus.  
    
    When Initiating a new Hangout, perhaps there can be a checkbox for the pair to mark the session as open or closed.
    When the user hovers over 'his' hangout, show the 'Restart Hangout" link, as well as the 'edit' button to the right.
